<a href="javascript:card_browser(146)">Morgul Skulker</a> x2<br>
Total- 32  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> Review Update: Thank you to all who have actually read the deck and strategy and reviewed the deck honestly. Most of the reviews have been helpful in some way.<br>
<br><br>
<br><br>
Introduction<br>
<br><br>
<br><br>
Aragorn and Legolas are your archers. Gandalf clears the adventure path of conditions and uses Strength of Spirit to keep exertion tokens off of your archers. <br>
<br><br>
<br><br>
Your Nazgul minions come out fast and fierce using Morgul Gates to minimize cost and Blade Tips to slow the opponent to a crawl.<br>
<br><br>
<br><br>
Top cards for this deck:<br>
<br><br>
<br><br>
Important cards for the fellowship side would be Servant of The Secret Fire, which allows you to battle any high vitality minions that make it through the archery phase alive. The character weapons, Glamdring and Ranger Sword are also very important for that same reason. Barlimann Butterburr is also a key card. Exerting him gets the very important Strength of Spirit or Servant of The Secret Fire back into your hand.<br>
<br><br>
<br><br>
Important Shadow cards would be Morgul Gates which reduces the cost of Nazgul minions by 2. Blade Tips are very powerful, wounding that character every fellowship phase and combined with Black Breath makes that character not heal! Fear is a great card also. It discards an ally of your choice which can be critical if the opponent is relying on Thrarin to block or a Bounder to save Frodo.<br>
<br><br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
How this Deck Beats you<br>
<br><br>
<br><br>
This deck can win several different ways. If you are able to win the bid, you will want the opponent to go first. This makes him move to your sites, The Weatherhills, and Ford of Bruinen. These are Nazgul havens. All of the Nazgul are fierce or can be made fierce so I feel these are the best sites to play for this deck. This deck can overwhelm people very quickly if they are unprepared. Morgul Gates help your minions come out very quickly and cheaply. Ulaire Nelya comes out at site 2 and can convert sites if necessary. If the opponent lives through site 2 and 3. Just reload your hand for site 5 and let them have it again.<br>
<br><br>
<br><br>
The Nazgul slows the opponent down a lot, especially if a blade tip has been delivered. They just can&#39;t move very fast and give up a lot of twilight to a Nazgul deck.<br>
<br><br>
<br><br>
Your fellowship side is designed for survivability through balance, aimed archery, and condition removal. Gandalf in any deck with his support cards and characters balances any deck. Any deck without Gandalf is missing a key element to the game. Being able to remove any conditions is very good. Albert Dreary also can remove Moria and Urak Hai conditions making those decks much less efficient and easier to handle.<br>
<br><br>
<br><br>
The aimed archery in the deck is very powerful. Legolas and Aragorn shoot down almost any minion that comes down. Aragorn and Gandalf, when armed with swords, can handle any minions you don&#39;t kill with archery. Your fellowship can march along the adventure path almost without a care in the world when this deck is setup correctly. When moving from sites 7, 8, or to 9, A Rangers Versatility and archery can be the game winning combination for you.<br>
<br><br>
<br><br>
Number 1 Card<br>
<br><br>
<br><br>
Strength of Spirit is the most important card for this deck. It minimizes putting exertion tokens on any of your characters, but most importantly, your archers, allowing them to use their aimed archery as often as possible. It also can be used on any other companions if they are forced to exert.<br>
<br><br>
<br><br>
Thanks for reviewing and enjoy playing this deck.       </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=20957"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=20957" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td></tr></table></td></tr></table> <!-- #EndEditable --></td>
